subject: p15758946
Findings: Right internal jugular central venous catheter tip terminates in the upper SVC. Left-sided Port-A-Cath tip terminates in the cavoatrial junction. Cardiac, mediastinal and hilar contours are stable with unfolding of the thoracic aorta. Surgical chain sutures are noted within the right mid lung field with adjacent scarring. No pleural effusion or pneumothorax is visualized. Multiple clips are seen within the left upper abdomen, compatible with prior nephrectomy. There are old right-sided rib fractures.
Impression: Right internal jugular central venous catheter tip in the upper SVC without pneumothorax.
